{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-03215/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-03215"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:32:15"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["full shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["exterior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, tilt"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["three shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man and woman walk down a cobblestone road, holding hands."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03215/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-03215","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03215/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-03215"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03215/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03215/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03215/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03215/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03215/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03215/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03215/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03215/canvas/1/1dacb621-94d7-4465-ae2d-5c30f2d16ea3","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T13:58:46.899Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>This scene was filmed on High Street in Staithes, North Yorkshire. The composition evokes the <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW4376682 BCX4\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Freewheelin%27_Bob_Dylan#/media/File:Bob_Dylan_-_The_Freewheelin'_Bob_Dylan.jpg\"><u>album cover</u></a> of Bob Dylan’s <em>The Freewheelin' Bob Dylan</em>, which features Dylan and his then-girlfriend Suze Rotolo. The pair finds themselves nearly alone on a street that is normally crowded; this staging gives the sense that Reynolds and Alma now occupy a world of their own. The only person whom they pass is an older woman. If one of the central conflicts in their relationship is the tension between Alma and Cyril, then this shot may signify how they will move past Reynolds’s sibling on their own, with Alma replacing both Cyril and the memory of Reynolds’s mother.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03215/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:891.6504854368937,435.92233009708684,523.4951456310681,537.47572815534"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03215/canvas/1/76796158-ec2c-4de4-986c-48a57b18a183","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T13:59:06.585Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The voiceover is not grounded in another shot of Alma’s conversation with Dr. Hardy. Nonetheless, viewers are reminded that the film in its entirety may be a recounting narrated by Alma.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03215/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:132.0388349514568,109.7087378640772,408.54368932038835,233.009708737864"}}}]}]}]}